External knowledge: 
Top scorer refers to the player with the highest number of goals scored in a specific season; 
each team has its own ranking of top scorers, and this query is looking for the team name of the player who is ranked #1 in their respective team.

sql:
SELECT team_id, games_played
FROM standings
WHERE team_id = 1;

SELECT team_id, SUM(games_played) AS total_games_played
FROM standings
GROUP BY team_id;

SELECT SUM(games_played) AS total_games_played
FROM standings
WHERE team_id = 1 AND season_id = 1;
